records.addlTxt:
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Maintain fulltime employment;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
9)  pay restitution of $5,311.70 to Walmart, joint and several with Eric Newcomer;
10) spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
Minutes.
